				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Non-tradable, easy to get &quot;must haves&quot;?<a name="68304"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Oct 27 04 1:51 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Tiny Cloak of Darkest Night, this is an item you will use all the time.  Even though our invis no longer kills pets (the primary reason I got this in the first place), it is still so nice.  You can invis yourself without memming a song (worth its weight in gnomes), as well a fast cast time.  
<br />

<br />
Other items I always carry:
<br />

<br />
<a target="_new" href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=473">http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=473</a>
<br />
Workers Sledgemallet from OT - Free gate when I run out of reagents and I need a ride.  Pair this with SS Helm if you dont have something friendly to beat on.  It can take awhile, but ghetto punt better than nothing.
<br />

<br />
<a target="_new" href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=17786">http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=17786</a>
<br />
Binden Concertia - Gate neck is invaluable. Reagents cost 130ish plat, but it is so worth it.  This is a EP level camp, so only doable with that level of PoP access.
<br />

<br />
<a target="_new" href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=8280">http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=8280</a>
<br />
Wand of Imperceptibility from The Deep - Shink Wand!  Need I say more?  No more lugging around vanishing devices, batteries, and toolboxes.
<br />

<br />
All I can think of off the top of my head as soloable or duoable for a bard.
<br />
</span></td>
