				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Non-tradable, easy to get &amp;quot;must haves&amp;quot;?<a name="68649"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Nov 1 04 12:00 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I just camped the shrink wand this weekend.  I took a major break right through Luclin so the Deep was mostly new to me.
<br />

<br />
I cannot see how this could be solo'ed well.  None of the though horror model mobs are mezzable or charmable.  The regular horror's are lullable, but you have 3 mobs and then 5 more afterwards.  And there were 6 others nearby.  Make sure to approach from the north, because elder thought horrors in the south.  These are vicious and cannot be lulled (or mezzed, and prob flagged uncharmable, but I don't have new charm to test :p).
<br />

<br />
With a 66 warrior it was not too bad.  The warrior would lose health with straight melee horrors, but then go back to 100% with casters and swapping in a 3.2 mod lute (Make sure to twist in PoV :p)
<br />

<br />
All of this is in tight quarters, so snare is a huge MUST.  Also, the named cannot be snared!  I got around this by making sure to pull a trash mob before the named got to &lt;20%.  a pita when I needed to keep pov up and the trash could not be mezed :/
<br />

<br />
All and all it was a fun experience and also got Inscribable words for the VP silverwing quest.</span></td>
