				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Non-tradable, easy to get &quot;must haves&quot;?<a name="68751"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Nov 2 04 9:26 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>&quot;Hobbit mask is easier? I hear nightmares of guys camping that for months. Most people I know get the wand in a few hours.&quot;
<br />

<br />
I meant easier than the Dwarf and no-longer-dropping Gnome masks 8-)
<br />

<br />
&quot;I would have to agree, getting the halfling mask is nothing short of a nightmare. I would take the 8 ST clearings it took me to get dwarf mask then ever trying to do halfling mask again.&quot;
<br />

<br />
And did you solo your ST key, and solo the 8 ST clearings? 8-)
<br />

<br />
Sure with a big raiding guild behind you who are willing to keep clearing it then maybe the Dwarf mask is easier, but not everyone has that! In terms of resources needed to acquire, the Hobbit mask is orders of magnitude easier, it simply requires patience. Lots and lots of patience, admittedly, took me 5 days of camping to get, but at least I could camp it. Which is, in fact, still quicker than 8 ST clearings 8-)
<br />

<br />
'Easy' is a relative term, of course, and what is considered easy for some is impossible for others, but generally what I would consider easy is something doable with a single group of non-uber characters (or less, eg soloable). And as the original post asked for 'easy to get' items, I personally would rule out raid areas 8-)
<br />

<br />
I was in a big raiding guild for several years, but I eventually quit as I really didn't enjoy raiding, I was only there because all my friends were, and that guild has since imploded anyway, so now my usual resources are what my sister, her other half and I can play between us, which is currently:-
<br />

<br />
66 SK (me), 66 Bard (me), 66 Cleric (sister), 66 Enchanter (sister), 70 SK (sister's other half) and 67 Shaman (sister's other half)
<br />

<br />
All are in Bazaar/LDoN gear, most under 100 AAs.
<br />

<br />
I can also play a 62 Cleric and a 65 Shaman if we're doing something a bit tougher, but as you can see we're pretty limited in what we can attempt, but it's still a lot more fun than raiding 8-)
<br />

<br />
So, if it's something I could get, with my very limited resources, then I'd agree it's easy, otherwise it's hard to impossible 8-)
<br />

<br />
Katawarl, standing up for the non-raiding few 8-)
<br />
